<br>
We don't yet have the capability to target individuals in most instances.  We don't yet have the capacity to even know who's guilty and who's innocent all of the time.<br>
<br>
We DO know, however, that Osama Bin Ladin was the mastermind behind several terrorist attacks against America.<br>
<br>
We DO know that he has been very outspoken about killing Americans.<br>
<br>
We DO know that the Taliban has harbored him for the past 10 years or so and that they are protecting him now.<br>
<br>
We strongly suspect that he masterminded, or at least supported this latest attack.  I believe that our government has proof.<br>
<br>
This attack was an act of war.  There is no other way to interpret it.  There is no way to back down from that aside from pure, unadulterated cowardice.<br>
<br>
War is not pretty.  Nobody should have to go through it.  But when it comes time for it, it has to happen.<br>
<br>
A war was NEEDED to stop the Nazis from slaughtering millions.  It happened and it was effective.<br>
<br>
A war was NEEDED to stop the Japanese from raping, torturing and murdering their way through the pacific rim.  It happened and it was effective.<br>
<br>
A war was NEEDED to stop &quot;ethnic clensing&quot; in the balklands.  It happened and it was effective.<br>
<br>
A war was NEEDED to beat Saddam Hussain back out of Kuwait.  It happened, and it was effective in that goal, at least.<br>
<br>
In each and every one of those conflicts there were civilian casualties.  Sadly that's just the way war goes.  The only good thing that can be said about war today as compared to then is that the technology has improved enough so that we can significantly decrease the number of civilian casualties, as the more recent conflicts proved.<br>
<br>
Of course, we are fighting an enemy, in this case, that thinks nothing of hiding behind women and children to protect themeselves.  They think nothing of putting &quot;human shields&quot; around their military installations.  They consider it normal to manufacture chemical weapons in the same factories they make baby formula in. . .<br>
<br>
Don't for a second believe that if we just ignore this it will go away.<br>
<br>
Don't for a second think that these folks would be done if we pulled all of our troops back home.<br>
<br>
Don't for a second consider our support of Israel a factor, or our embargo of Iraq the deciding point.  We could stop both and still be subject to these attacks.<br>
<br>
We are at war, and we cannot half-ass or peacenik our way through it or we've lost before it starts.  And losing this war will result in civilian casualties that haven't even been hinted at thus far. . . <p><b>Filo</b> <BR>
